OL,6,FMethods for capturing hate crime are
OL,7,Fnot consistent across forces, so the
OL,8,Fdata cannot be used to compare
OL,9,Fdirectly the number of offences
OL,10,Fbetween different areas or provide an
OL,11,Foverall total for the whole of England.
OL,13,FData obtained from smaller forces, or
OL,14,Fthose covering areas with few towns or
OL,15,Fcities, typically showed low numbers
OL,16,Fof offences, often in single figures,
OL,17,Fmeaning a month-on-month trend was
OL,18,Fhard to determine.
